### Tested versions

Reproducible in 4.5 master and 4.4.stable

### System information

Godot v4.4.stable.mono - macOS Sequoia (15.3.2) - Multi-window, 2 monitors - Metal (Mobile) - integrated Apple M4 Pro (Apple9) - Apple M4 Pro (12 threads)

### Issue description

When attempting to use `CanvasItem` shader instance uniforms inside custom functions, there're tons of shader compilation error messages thrown out in the editor output, and instance uniforms do not work while parameters have appeared in the inspector.
It seems that this issue only occurs in RD based pipelines, on Compatibility everything works well.


```glsl
shader_type canvas_item;

instance uniform float test = 0.0f;

float test_function(float x)
{
	return x * test;
}

void fragment() {
	COLOR.rgb *= test_function(1.0);
}
```


![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4c18e8af-9ce2-4dd9-9ac0-db6e082f43b5)

### Steps to reproduce

Open the MRP project, and see the output. Also sprites' color in the viewport won't be changed by their instance shader parameters.

